1 this title for payment of any location damages due which the
2 operator cannot otherwise pay. The Secretary of State shall hold
3 such corporate surety bond, letter of credit from a banking
4 institution, cash or certificate of deposit for the benefit of the
5 surface owners of this state and shall ensure that such security is
6 in a form readily payable to a surface owner awarded damages in an
7 action brought pursuant to this act. Each corporate surety bond,
8 letter of credit, cash, or certificate of deposit filed with the
9 Secretary of State shall be accompanied by a filing fee of Ten
10 Dollars ($10.00).
11 B. The bonding company or banking institution shall file, for
12 such fee as is provided for by law, a certificate that said bond or
13 letter of credit is in effect or has been canceled, or that a claim
14 has been made against it in the office of the court clerk in each
15 county in which the operator is drilling or planning to drill. Said
16 bond or letter of credit must remain in full force and effect as
17 long as the operator continues drilling operations in this state.
18 Each such filing shall be accompanied by a filing fee of Ten Dollars
19 ($10.00).
20 C. Upon deposit of the bond, letter of credit, cash, or
21 certificate of deposit, the operator shall be permitted entry upon
22 the property and shall be permitted to commence drilling of a well
23 in accordance with the terms and conditions of any lease or other
24 existing contractual or lawful right.
